This paper is about neural architecture search (NAS) for image classification tasks, which falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method uses evolutionary algorithms, which is a common technique in optimization problems and falls under the category of neural evolution (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of non-dominated sorting, which is a technique commonly used in multi-objective optimization problems and falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY).
